24th Street at S.E. corner of Lexington Avenue, showing old stables and harness companies.
February 4, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

Lexington Avenue, west side, north from East 24th Street. View No. 2 is limited to the blockfront extending to 25th Street. The three larger buildings in the midground are, an office structure at the S. W. corner of East 26th Street, the 69th Regiment Armory and the American Book Co. Building. The latter is at the N. W. corner of East 27th Street. In the background, at 42nd Street, appears the towering Chanin and Chrysler Buildings.
